with innovative healthcare technology

 

As the Clinical and Research Informatics Division of the Department of Medicine at Massachusetts General Hospital, the Laboratory of Computer Science explores innovative applications of information technology in healthcare. We put people at the heart of technology and enable collaborations that improve healthcare delivery, research, and education.

Learn more about LCS →

 

Our Projects

LCS projects and research address a wide range of healthcare-related needs including patient engagement, information management, decision support, provider workflows, medical education, and clinical research.

 

Learn more about our projects →

 
 

Our Partners & Collaborators

Our primary partners are a diverse set of clinical groups at Massachusetts General Hospital as well as other hospitals at Partners Healthcare. Industry collaborations allow us to make selected technologies commercially available to the broader healthcare industry while maintaining our focus on continual innovation.

 
 

Learn more about collaborations with LCS →

Projects

We rapidly translate research into operational system designs that have a daily impact on clinicians, researchers, patients, and educators.

Learn More →

 

PartnerShips

We work with professionals in business, healthcare and technology to extend our ideas, designs, and applications to the healthcare industry.

Learn More →

Teaching

We participate in a post-doctoral training fellowship in medical informatics as part of the Harvard Informatics Research Training Program.

Learn More →
